description.p:
i) a sac formed of deformable material and comprising an outer layer; and
ii) a filler inside the sac;
wherein, the filler comprises a material with a coefficient of friction that allows opposite sides of the sac to move relative to one another when a force is applied to the joint, and an outer surface of the sac is arranged not to move relative to the joint component surface it is in contact with, during articulation.
